President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint two individuals to key positions in his Administration. Christopher Paul Henzel, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, will be appointed as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Yemen. Henzel has been an American diplomat since 1985 and currently serves as Deputy Chief of Mission at the American Embassy in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. He has also held various leadership positions at the United States Department of State and has served in multiple United States missions overseas. Henzel is a recipient of several notable State Department awards and speaks Arabic, Spanish, and German.

